Lucilia thatuna
is an uncommon western North American species, which has been collected from California, Colorado, Idaho, Oregon, Utah, Wyoming, and Washington (
Whitworth 2006 , see also Appendix 1
). The biology of this species remains unknown (
Hall 1948
), however it likely parasitizes anurans, since it is usually collected in areas around marshes and streams (T. Whitworth, unpublished data).
